# Editing this capsule

The server reads .gmi files directly off disk -- no rebuild required
after editing. There are two ways to change what this capsule serves:

## 1. File-browser app (easy)

If you have the openhost-filestash (or equivalent) file-browser app
installed in this compute space, open it and navigate to the
"gemini" app's data directory. You'll find a "content/" folder with
the .gmi files you see here. Edit, save, refresh your Gemini client.

## 2. oh app exec (power user)

You can edit files directly from the shell using the OpenHost CLI:

```
oh app exec gemini -- sh -c 'cat > /data/app_data/gemini/content/index.gmi'
```

(Paste your new content, Ctrl-D.)

